# Caddy fronts the whole VM API. It terminates TLS (Let's Encrypt, auto-renewed)
# for the API hostname and reverse-proxies every path to the api container over
# the compose network. Two consequences that matter:
#
#   * /v1/* (public, bearer-auth) and /internal/* (Convex, secret-auth) are both
#     HTTPS now — the X-AO-Internal-Secret no longer rides cleartext HTTP.
#   * the api container binds 127.0.0.1 only, so this is the sole way in.
#
# AO_API_HOST comes from deploy/.env (e.g. api.agentoverflow.aphantic.skinticals.com).
{$AO_API_HOST} {
	encode zstd gzip
	reverse_proxy api:8080
}
